<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Myuzi is an app for streaming music from YouTube. It&#39;s intended as an alternative to Spotify. It doesn&#39;t require an account, has no ads and uses GTK for its interface. Several installation methods are available (see below).</p> <p>Reviews:</p> <ul> <li><a href="https://youtu.be/VUPLdBMYOLY?t=1189">Linux Saloon</a></li> </ul> <hr/> <p><strong>v0.9.1</strong>:</p> <ul> <li>Fixed radio autoplay setting</li> </ul> <p><strong>v0.9.0</strong>:</p> <ul> <li><p>Added song and playlist downloading</p></li> <li><p>Added online/offline mode</p></li> <li><p>Added &quot;autoplay similar songs after queue ends&quot; setting (radio)</p></li> <li><p>Added tooltips to almost all buttons</p></li> <li><p>Removed (broken) mute setting</p></li> <li><p>Fixed issues caused by invalid import data</p></li> </ul> <hr/> <p><strong>Install:</strong> <a href="https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/myuzi">AUR</a> | <a href="https://gitlab.com/zehkira/myuzi/-/raw/master/flatpak/myuzi.flatpak?inline=false">Flatpak</a> | <a href="https://gitlab.com/zehkira/myuzi/-/blob/master/INSTALL.md#install-from-source">From source</a></p> <p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://gitlab.com/zehkira/myuzi">GitLab</a></p> <p><strong>Donations:</strong> <a href="https://www.patreon.com/bePatron?u=65739770">Patreon</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zehkira"> /u/zehkira </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w22knz/myuzi_music_streaming_app_v091_song_downloading/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w22knz/myuzi_music_streaming_app_v091_song_downloading/">[comments]</a></span>